@startuml
title Cloud Bursting Architecture - Burst-Out and Burst-In

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Service\nConsumer A" as SCA
actor "Service\nConsumer B" as SCB
actor "Service\nConsumer C" as SCC

node "On-Premises Environment" as OnPrem {
  component "Service A\n(on-premises)" as SA
  database "State management\ndatabase (on-prem)" as DB1
  component "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
}

cloud "Cloud Environment" as Cloud {
  component "Cloud Service A\n(redundant, predeployed,\ninactive until burst)" as CSA
  database "State management\ndatabase (cloud)" as DB2
  component "Pay-Per-Use Monitor" as PPM
}

SCA --> ASL
SCB --> ASL
SCC --> ASL

ASL --> SA : within capacity\nthreshold
ASL --> CSA : (1) burst-out:\nredirect when threshold exceeded

DB1 <..> DB2 : (2) resource replication\nkeeps state synchronized

PPM ..> CSA : tracks cloud usage\nfor billing

note right of CSA
  Cloud-based resources are released
  ("burst in") when no longer required;
  no further cloud usage fees incurred.
end note

note bottom of ASL
  Automated scaling listener determines
  when to redirect requests to cloud-based
  IT resources.
end note

@enduml

